title: FT: T206 Bell Follow Through Wet Transfer and Other Low Grade Cards
author: Idiottax

posts.post_title: FT: T206 Bell Follow Through Wet Transfer and Other Low Grade Cards
posts.post_content:
In the course of putting together my low grade T206 set, I've come across some doubles, either through the purchase of lots or through accidental purchase.  Ideally, I'd like to trade some of my doubles for other cards I need for my set and have put together a list of what I have available.  

Below is the picture of the Bell Follow Through with a Sweet Caporal Wet Transfer on the front.  

[IMG]http://i1236.photobucket.com/albums/ff453/Idiottax/For%20Trade/BellWetTransferFront.jpg[/IMG]

[URL="http://s1236.photobucket.com/albums/ff453/Idiottax/For%20Trade/"]For Trade[/URL]

Aside from the from the Bell, most are lower grade commons, though there are two Zimmermans in the album, because I am having a hard time figuring out which one to keep.  

Bell (Follow Through)
Camnitz (Arms Crossed)
Dahlen (Boston)
Fletcher
Ganley
Graham
Howell (Portrait)
Mattern
Nattress
Oldring
Randall
Raymond
Snodgrass
Zimmerman

[URL="http://s1236.photobucket.com/albums/ff453/Idiottax/For%20Trade%20Flaking/"]For Trade Flaking[/URL]

These cards all came from the same lots and are starting to have some flaking or other major condition issues.  The Tinker (Hands on Knees) is really my idea of what a filler card could be.

Brain
Crandall (No Cap)
Dubuc
Stephens
Tenney
Tinker (Hands on Knees)
Titus
Wiltse

If anyone is interested, let me know and I can send along my needs list, since I am just north of the halfway point in completing the set.
